Description: Movie recommendations powered by tweets
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Mombo collects tweets about movies from Twitter and performs textual analysis (using natural language processing techniques) of the text to determine positive, negative, mixed, neutral sentiment. It then determines a movie rating based on the counts of positive, negative, mixed sentiment tweets. This is the overall crowd rating for the movie. The retrieval of tweets from Twitter and computation of sentiment is done in near real-time. Besides the crowd rating, the service also provides personalized recommendations to individual users. The Mombo recommendation engine uses collaborative filtering techniques to suggest movies based on movies a user has liked in the past. The recommendation system also shows the movies liked by a majority of the users' friends who saw those movies.
Industry Groups: Data and Analytics, Internet Services, Media and Entertainment

Description: Exodus Online Services is an internet service provider company.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Exodus Online Services wasn’t always an ISP. Back in 1987, Cliff Stegman, their father, left his former company to join with his sons David and Jim, and his son-in-law Eddie Lutz, to form the C. Stegman Co., Inc. Their mission back then was to be a software development house for the Apple Macintosh. Soon after they added a dba of Exodus Software, under which they published Retriever, ExpressWrite, and Retriever II. They all received excellent reviews from the Mac Press. Youngest son Dan joined the company in 1989. As Exodus Software they also did work as Macintosh Consultants, with expertise in 4th Dimension, MItemView, HyperCard as well as traditional programming work in Pascal and MacApp. In 1995 they decided they wanted to try something new. After much research, they put their skills towards becoming an Internet Service Provider. As Cincinnati’s third local ISP, they opened back in June 1995. Since then, they have always prided ourself on providing personal, friendly service to their clients. In July 2008, they refocused the business towards web hosting and development and moved their base of operations from Finneytown Ohio to Fairfield Ohio. In 2018 Dan decided to close the doors and move on to new adventures.

Description: Polltopia is a tech startup that enables individuals to segment and analyze data by deploying polls on social media channels.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: What is Polltopia? Naturally, it depends on whom you ask. In Argentina, they might call it innovative. Those 25 and under may say it’s game-changing. Meanwhile, the majority of Nebraskans could decide that it’s a revolution. But why take our word for it… why not just ask them for yourself? With Polltopia, you’ll be equipped with that exact ability—to ask anything to anybody. You’re able to create an unlimited amount of polls for the world to vote in. Then, you can view statistical information about the people that voted in your poll. You can see that in a certain poll, 75% of men voted one way as opposed to 25% of women, or that New York voted much more in favor of a certain option than Texas did, or that those who were 45 and older tended to vote with some sort of consistency, different than that of their younger counterparts. Use this information for your research, curiosity, or pure enjoyment. Users are also able to comment on polls, so everything doesn’t have to be so black and white (or green, yellow, pink, blue or red, depending on how many options you decide to put in your poll). As a voter, use Polltopia to allow your voice to be heard. Democracy does exist in this world, but not to the extent in which people all over can be represented regarding any number of issues—from an extremely important and sensitive political stance, to a mere preference in sodas. Polltopia effectively does one thing: it gives power, influence, and potential back to the people.
Industry Groups: Data and Analytics, Design, Internet Services, Media and Entertainment

Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: ExpertBids allows entrepreneurs and businesses to get personalized bids on any legal, accounting or consulting need they may have.  Clients (anyone who needs a professional service provider) can anonymously post their need, including the location and description (a "Service Request"). The posting can then be viewed by applicable, pre-screened, lawyers, accountants or consultants ("Experts"). If interested, the Experts can send the Client either a flat fee or hourly price quote and a description.  The Client can then view this along with the Expert's profile, rating and past client reviews. The Expert's profile includes their license information, educational background, location, websites, and other information about the Expert. Based on this information, the Client can decide to whether to work with any of the Experts, get more information from any Expert, or do nothing - there are no obligations. ExpertBids.com launched in November 2010, and remodeled in September of 2011, and has tens of thousands of Experts and Clients from all over the U.S.  The site has been mentioned in large national media publications including the Wall Street Journal, USA Today, GigaOm, Inc.com, NBC, and Business Insider.

Currently the low-end market is dominated by national brands, such as Cost Cutters, Great Clips, or brands such as Massage Envy. Consumers in this market segment are looking for high-quality green or organic products administered by highly trained service providers. High-quality green services and brands are the fastest growing segment of this industry. Through their unique strategic partnership with the Aveda brand, their signature training, and synergistic business model, Pureflection will provide consumers the quality of service and products they desire which is currently lacking as an industry standard.  Pureflection will focus on the development of their flagship Aveda lifestyle salon & spa models. This location will offer salon and spa services from haircuts & color to massage, facials, and body treatments. This location will be approximately 4,600 sq. ft. and generate gross revenue of $750k - $1.5 million with net profit margins of 8-22%. They will position their services as 5-star value at 4-star prices through their use of their VIP membership program, which will provide a more consistent cash flow model than the typical standalone salon and spa model. Additionally, services and guest experiences are positioned to exceed their competitors’ and their clients’ expectations, by providing many low-cost, value-added, complimentary add-ons to their services and experiences.
